               <p>London Cases, Second Jury.</p>
               <p>Before Mr. Common Sergeant.</p>
               <p>1577. 
               <persName id="t18250915-352-defend1779" type="defendantName">
                  JAMES 
                  HERBERT
               <interp inst="t18250915-352-defend1779" type="surname" value="HERBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-defend1779" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-defend1779" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-defend1779" type="age" value="19"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18250915-352-off1907" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-off1907" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-off1907" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18250915-352-cd1908" type="crimeDate">10th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-352-off1907 t18250915-352-cd1908"></join>, a handkerchief, value 5 s., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18250915-352-victim1780" type="victimName">
                        Henry 
                        Barnes
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-victim1780" type="surname" value="Barnes"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18250915-352-victim1780" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18250915-352-victim1780" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-352-off1907 t18250915-352-victim1780"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>HENRY BARNES. On the evening of the 10th of July, I was walking towards <placeName id="t18250915-352-crimeloc1909">Temple-bar</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-352-crimeloc1909" type="placeName" value="Temple-bar"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-352-crimeloc1909" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-352-off1907 t18250915-352-crimeloc1909"></join>. I felt a person's hand in my pocket - I turned round, and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief in his hand, putting it into his bosom. I seized him, called the watchman, and gave charge of him - he threw it down as I seized him. I took it up, and gave it to the watchman - it was in my hand not ten minutes before - no other person was near.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Was it not possible for it to have fallen from your pocket? A. It was possible.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-352-person1781">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COX
               <interp inst="t18250915-352-person1781" type="surname" value="COX"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-person1781" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-person1781" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard an alarm, and took the prisoner - he denied the charge, but said another person did it who passed by.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-352-person1782">
                  THOMAS 
                  HODMAN
               <interp inst="t18250915-352-person1782" type="surname" value="HODMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-person1782" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-person1782" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was officer of the night. I received this handkerchief at the watch-house.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Mr. Barnes put the handkerchief into his pocket; I was on the same side of the way, and saw it drop - I took it up - he turned round and seized me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18250915-352-verdict1910" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-352-verdict1910" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
